transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Jimmy. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'd like to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay. Let me see if I can pull you up and see if I can help you with that.

Speaker 2: I'm sure I can. Bear with me one second.

Speaker 1: Okay. Can I have someone to speak to, please?

Speaker 2: Fred Heidman.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Mr. Heidman. Okay. I was able to pull up your information here.

Speaker 2: I see that you're currently getting the Viagra 50-milligram.

Speaker 1: It looks like that you're getting 10 of them, your prescription, every month.

Speaker 2: Is there any particular reason why you want to cancel today, Mr. Heidman?

Speaker 1: If you don't mind me asking.

Speaker 2: Just have a bunch of extra.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Just don't need that many.

Speaker 1: Okay. I can appreciate that.

Speaker 2: What I'd like to do for you so you can keep your prescription active,

Speaker 1: we can postpone it and pause it so you're not getting them every month.

Speaker 2: So, therefore, you can keep your prescription active.

Speaker 1: And what that does, that allows you to, when you get caught up,

Speaker 2: you can actually order when you want and still keep the discounted price that

Speaker 1: you have because you know our pills do come from the Pfizer labs in France.

Speaker 2: And when the tests kick in, they're going to go up like three times as much.

Speaker 1: But by you having an active prescription on file,

Speaker 2: you will keep that same grandfathered in price.

Speaker 1: So I can, like, postpone it for like six months.

Speaker 2: And, therefore, when you want to order, you can always order.

Speaker 1: Or if six months happen to come too quick for you,

Speaker 2: you can always call like you're doing now and push it back a few more months

Speaker 1: so that it keeps your prescription active,

Speaker 2: and you won't get them as regularly as every month.

Speaker 1: So can I go ahead and do that for you?

Speaker 2: So a question with that is do I have to call to activate it

Speaker 1: or does it activate itself again after?

Speaker 2: It stays active, so that means you can call any time in between then.

Speaker 1: And I will actually give you a date too as well where you can call before that

Speaker 2: date and say, hey, I'm not ready for them yet, push them back some more.

Speaker 1: But you won't get them every month going forward.

Speaker 2: I'm setting you up on a six-month plan so that gives you more control to whenever

Speaker 1: you want to order in between those six months.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: And that will keep your prescription active.

Speaker 2: Go ahead.

Speaker 1: My question is in order to receive more in the future, do I have to make a call

Speaker 2: or does it start automatically after a certain – after a set date?

Speaker 1: On July 28th, if we haven't heard from you, you will get ten additional pills,

Speaker 2: and then it will be paused again for another six months.

Speaker 1: So it will be every six months.

Speaker 2: That's what I'm setting you up now so your prescription will be active.

Speaker 1: So I have a date of July 28th.

Speaker 2: That's six months from now.

Speaker 1: Okay, we can give that a try.

Speaker 2: Okay, not a problem.

Speaker 1: I just took care of that for you.

Speaker 2: And like I said, again, that allows you to order in between that time,

Speaker 1: or if you want to pause it later, you can always call us

Speaker 2: and say push me back a few more months.

Speaker 1: I still have some left because the pills have a shelf life of three years.

Speaker 2: Okay?

Speaker 1: Sure.

Speaker 2: Okay, very good.

Speaker 1: Not a problem.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
